            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#VM">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>ἀνεπαύσα<supplied reason="lost">το</supplied> <persName type="attested"><name><supplied reason="lost">Θεό</supplied>
                    <lb n="2"/>δοῦλος</name></persName> <expan><abbr><hi rend="supraline">Ἰ</hi></abbr><ex>ησοῦ</ex><abbr><hi rend="supraline">ς</hi></abbr></expan> <supplied reason="lost"><expan><abbr>Χ</abbr><ex>ριστό</ex><abbr>ς</abbr></expan></supplied>
                    <lb n="3"/>νώνες Ἀ<gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><desc>month name</desc></gap>
                    <lb n="4"/>ζήσας ἔ<supplied reason="lost">τη</supplied> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"><desc>number of years</desc></gap>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus" resp="#JP">
                <listApp>
                    <app><note>Text after Ferrua</note></app>
                    <app loc="2"><note>Manni Piraino: δοῦλ<unclear>ο</unclear>ς Ἰ(η)σ(οῦ)</note></app>
                </listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p><!--translation(s) - add @xml:lang for 'en' or 'it' to div--></p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Ferrua rejects Manni Piraino's reading of line 2, noting that ΙΣ must be resolved in the nominative and that this most likely followed by an abbreviation (probably employing a christogram) for Christos. The missing month in line 3 must be either April or August.</p>
            </div>
